- cs.PL (Programming Languages): ASMs are a formal method for specifying and verifying programs, and this bibliography focuses on papers that deal with or use ASMs. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science): ASMs are based on a mathematical model of computation, and this bibliography includes papers that discuss the theoretical foundations of ASMs. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): ASMs can be used for software specification and verification, and this bibliography includes papers that discuss their application in software engineering. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): ASMs can be used to specify and analyze algorithms, and this bibliography includes papers that discuss their application in this area. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): ASMs can be used to model and reason about intelligent systems, and this bibliography includes papers that discuss their application in AI.
